---
// bracket glyphs are decorative only, no diagram
---

<section id="top" class="relative max-w-content mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-20 overflow-hidden">
  <span
    class="pointer-events-none select-none absolute -top-10 -left-4 font-mono text-[220px] leading-none text-ink-border/50"
    aria-hidden="true"
  >[</span>
  <span
    class="pointer-events-none select-none absolute -bottom-24 -right-4 font-mono text-[220px] leading-none text-ink-border/50 rotate-180"
    aria-hidden="true"
  >[</span>

  <div class="relative">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-5 flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-signal"></span>
      cloud &amp; application security engineer
    </p>

    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-6xl font-semibold leading-[1.1] tracking-tight max-w-2xl">
      I secure the path every request takes<span class="cursor-blink h-9 sm:h-12"></span>
    </h1>

    <p class="mt-6 max-w-xl text-paper-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Cloud network & application security consultant. WAF, CDN, Zero Trust and SASE
      architectures for enterprise clients — plus the vendor relationships and pre-sales
      work that turn a design into a signed contract.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a
        href="/#projects"
        class="font-mono text-sm px-5 py-3 bg-signal text-ink font-medium rounded-sm hover:brightness-110 transition"
      >
        See case studies →
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/omarrdaniel/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="font-mono text-sm px-5 py-3 border border-ink-border text-paper rounded-sm hover:border-trace transition"
      >
        LinkedIn ↗
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-4 border-t border-ink-border flex justify-between font-mono text-xs text-paper-muted/70">
      <span>Milan, IT</span>
      <span>Open to international roles</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
